<h2><a name="exp" id="exp">exp</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">double</span> exp<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> arg <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>

The exp() function returns e (2.7182818) raised to the argth power.
</p>

<p>
C++ also provides the following overloaded forms:

</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">float</span> exp<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">float</span> arg <span class="br0">&#41;</span>; <span class="co1">// same as expf() in C99</span>
    <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> exp<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> arg <span class="br0">&#41;</span>; <span class="co1">// same as expl() in C99</span></pre>
<p>
Related Topics: <a href="log" class="wikilink1" title="c:math:log">log</a>, <a href="pow" class="wikilink1" title="c:math:pow">pow</a>, <a href="sqrt" class="wikilink1" title="c:math:sqrt">sqrt</a>
</p>

</div>
